      "side": 1,
      "message": "nit: (We probably don\u0027t care, but...) Counting all tasks will make the flake-rate lower than it should be. Assuming 2 attempts and an actual flake-rate of 50%, we would see the following:\n - 50% would succeed on first attempt\n - 25% would fail on first attempt and succeed on the next attempt (2 tasks)\n - 25% would fail on both attempts (2 tasks)\n\nSo, over four commits, we should see on average:\nc1: S\nc2: S\nc3: F S\nc4: F F\nTotal: 1 flake, 6 tasks \u003d 17% flake rate, rather than 50%\n\nCounting only tasks with Attempt \u003d\u003d 0 should make this more accurate.\n\n(It would still give us a 25% flake rate rather than 50%, but I don\u0027t know how to fix that, and as the flake rate decreases, the fail-fail case becomes more and more unlikely.)",
